The paper deals with the computational complexity of approximating the partition function for two different models, the antiferromagnetic Ising model and the hard-core model. This falls under the area of computational complexity theory, which is covered by cs.CC. The paper also involves the analysis of certain graph structures, such as regular trees and bipartite graphs, which are topics in graph theory and discrete mathematics, covered by cs.DS and cs.DM respectively. The use of critical points and second moment calculations suggests a connection to statistical physics, which is covered by cs.GT. Finally, the paper involves approximation algorithms and the study of the uniqueness region of the infinite tree, which are topics in information theory, covered by cs.IT.
